Company Overview
HGGC Citadel Plastics Holdings, Inc., through its subsidiaries, manufactures and distributes thermoplastic compounds and thermoset resins. It offers custom compounded products, including polypropylene, polyethylene, acrylonitrile butadiene styrene, nylon, polycarbonate, polybutylene terephthalate, polyethylene terephthalate, and alloys. The company also provides plastic compounds and concentrates. Its products are used in large and small appliances, house wares, healthcare products, automotive, agriculture, indoor and outdoor lighting, home and garden, industrial and household electrical, construction, power tools, HVAC, and recreation and leisure. The company was founded in 2007 and is base...
HGGC Citadel Plastics Holdings, Inc., through its subsidiaries, manufactures and distributes thermoplastic compounds and thermoset resins. It offers custom compounded products, including polypropylene, polyethylene, acrylonitrile butadiene styrene, nylon, polycarbonate, polybutylene terephthalate, polyethylene terephthalate, and alloys. The company also provides plastic compounds and concentrates. Its products are used in large and small appliances, house wares, healthcare products, automotive, agriculture, indoor and outdoor lighting, home and garden, industrial and household electrical, construction, power tools, HVAC, and recreation and leisure. The company was founded in 2007 and is based in West Chicago, Illinois with manufacturing locations in Evansville, Indiana; West Chicago, Illinois; Bedford, Virginia; Houston, Texas; Perrysburg, Ohio; Guelph, Ontario; Hamburg, Germany; Istanbul, Turkey; Dongguan and Shanghai, China; Mexico City and Juarez, Mexico; and Rio Claro, Brazil. As of June 1, 2015, HGGC Citadel Plastics Holdings, Inc. operates as a subsidiary of A. Schulman, Inc.
