A. Schulman To Pay $800M For PE-Backed Citadel Plastics



        By Linda Chiem



					Law360, New York (March 16, 2015,  5:07 PM EDT) -- Plastic compounds and chemical maker A. Schulman Inc. said Monday that it will drop $800 million to acquire private equity-backed Citadel Plastics Holdings Inc., as it continues to expand and diversify its U.S. portfolio with the addition of a specialty plastics maker in high-margin markets.A. Schulman said it has entered into a definitive agreement to pay $800 million to acquire all of the issued and outstanding capital stock of Citadel from middle-market private equity firms HGGC and Charlesbank Capital Partners.The transaction allows Akron, Ohio-based...
				
